** Project Title:

Hotel Reservation System

** Project Overview:

The Hotel Reservation System is a Java-based console application that allows users to search, book, cancel, and manage hotel rooms.
This system was developed as part of the CodeAlpha Internship to demonstrate skills in Object-Oriented Programming (OOP), JDBC, and MySQL database integration.

The system provides complete room management, booking tracking, and payment simulation.

** Objectives of the Project:
To design a hotel management system using OOP principles.
To use MySQL database for storing room and booking details.
To allow users to perform operations such as Search, Book, Cancel, and View bookings.
To simulate a real-time hotel reservation process.
To implement persistent storage using JDBC.
** Features Implemented:
1. Search Available Rooms

Users can view all available rooms with:

Room ID
Category (Standard / Deluxe / Suite)
Price
2. Book a Room
Customer enters their name
Selects a room
Payment simulation is shown
Booking is stored in the database
Room availability automatically updates
3. Cancel a Booking
User enters Booking ID
System deletes booking and updates room availability
4. View All Bookings

Displays full booking details:

Booking ID
Customer Name
Room ID
Booking Date
Payment Status
** Technologies Used:
Java (Core + OOP)
JDBC
MySQL Database
Collections Framework
** Database Structure:

Two tables were used:

1. rooms
Column	Type	Description
room_id	INT	Unique ID
category	VARCHAR	Room Type
price	DOUBLE	Room Price
is_available	BOOLEAN	Availability
2. bookings
Column	Type	Description
booking_id	INT (Auto)	Primary Key
customer_name	VARCHAR	Name of customer
room_id	INT	Linked with rooms table
booking_date	VARCHAR	Date of booking
payment_status	VARCHAR	Success / Pending

** Working Process:
System connects to MySQL using JDBC
User selects an option from menu
Based on user choice, system performs CRUD operations on database:
SELECT (search and view)
INSERT (book room)
DELETE (cancel booking)
UPDATE (availability)
Results are displayed on console
Database ensures data is stored permanently
